definitions.definition: A large log to burn at the back of a fire.
An accumulation or buildup , especially of unfilled orders , unconsumed products or unfinished work .
examples: He went to work on Saturday to try to work through the backlog of papers on his desk.
Kyle purchased a new one despite having a backlog of video games that he hasn't played.

definitions.definition: A log containing text previously read, as in text-based video games or chat rooms .
